We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer’s Office:
Continue to demand settlement of tax liabilities from the identified taxpayers;
Document the main reasons why these remained uncollected for the past years;
Adopt corresponding strategies to address the specific concerns of the taxpayers; and
In coordination with the Provincial Treasury Office, avail of the administrative and legal remedies provided by law to enforce collection of the delinquent real property taxes.

We recommended that in line with existing regulations and for proper accounting of expenses within the period for which they relate,  Management:
•	Require the immediate submission of  liquidation documents for cash advances that are overdue;
•	Ensure full liquidation of cash advances at the end of the year; 
•	Refrain from granting cash advances to a single payee in behalf of others to encourage prompt liquidation and to be able to monitor who are not entitled to additional cash advances; and
•	Refrain from granting advances to personnel who are not  part of the organic manpower of the LGU in order to impose liquidation, as necessary.
